com.google.template.soy.pysrc.restricted

Interface SoyPySrcPrintDirective

  • All Superinterfaces:
    SoyPrintDirective
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BasicEscapeDirective, EscapeHtmlDirective

    public interface SoyPySrcPrintDirective
extends SoyPrintDirective
    Interface for a Soy print directive implemented for the Python Source backend.

    Important: This may only be used in implementing print directive plugins.

    • Method Detail

      • applyForPySrc

        PyExpr applyForPySrc(PyExpr value,
                     List<PyExpr> args)
        Applies this directive on the given string value.

        Important note when implementing this method: The string value may not yet have been coerced to a string. You may need to explicitly coerce it to a string expression using PyExpr.toPyString().

        Parameters:
        value - The value to apply the directive on. This value may not yet have been coerced to a string.
        args - The directive's arguments, if any (usually none).
        Returns:
        The resulting value.
